      • isValidDatabaseIdentifier

        public static boolean isValidDatabaseIdentifier(java.lang.String identifier)
        Make sure that the given database name is a valid database identifier. A valid database identifier starts with a character or '_', followed by letters, digits, or '_'. For 9.x, you can add '#' to the non-first characters, and the length increases from 18 to 128. Since the server version is unknown before connecting, don't check for length.
